rComments: She is amazing. Very good at presenting the material to the class in a clear way. So easy to understand if you read the textbook first then go to the lecture. Review the lecture note every time before you go to the class. I picked the smaller class session and to be honest, best class ever. Her office hour however, always long wait!

Clear Lectures. Bad Tester. Yu Adjusts her test difficulty based on class performance. Our Test1 class avg was high (70s). She reacted by making the next one nigh impossible. Vagueries in interpretation, and an exceedingly hard opener seem her weapons of choice.  Nobody got above 74 in T2. T2 classavg 37. Beware. She also seems very sensitive.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'EXTRA CREDIT', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: for those lectures... you have to go to make some notes, so you understand what the course is about. but she never tests on what's on the lecture.
Very organized course structure. Lectures are clear. She explains concepts perfectly. But the tests are pretty tough. Class avg can be 70 something in one test and 40-50 something in another

Tests and quizzes were easy and fair. You can go to class and just forget about the textbook. Her lecture notes are very neat and complete. Final exam was verryyy difficult in comparison to the rest of the course.

Probably the best one in the economics department. Super clear, consistent and organized. Way better than other 4 economics profs I have ever had. Always willing to help and get feedback from students. Easy quizzes, fair tests, but her exam was just brutal.
Awesome professor. By far the best prof I have had at UTM. Very clear, concise notes. Tutorial questions are hard but once you solve them, they follow a pattern which usually reappears on tests.

She's very clear, tries her best to help you out as much as possible, and easy to follow. Her tests are similar to the tutorial problems she assigns. As long as you attend her lectures and take good notes, you'll get a mark above 80. Skipping lectures will lead to bad marks as everything piles on to each other. Also yes, she's really cute and hot.

I've heard a lot about how hard her tests, especially finals are, but my mark turned out to be pretty good in the course. Her lecture notes are really clear and the tutorial worksheets are a very good indicator of what's going to be on the tests. Her tests are definitely not easy, but there are a lot of part marks given.

I took eco202 two years back and at the beginning I was getting a 95% in the class, and the 2nd and 3rd tests got very harder - I ended up with a B in the final. Exam is really easy compared to the tests (but you gotta prepare well). I would recommend this prof to other students.

What can I say about this course that hasn't already been said by the other comments? ECO204 is not an easy course. Her test are nothing like the tutorial questions. It really tests your understanding of the topics and how to apply them. If you can avoid this course for ECO200, do it. If not, good luck to you!
easy to understand and follow in class, tests are from mars

tests are so unpredictable and stupid (only a couple of questions with a lot of weight)- doesnt teach the material on the tests in the class , or assign any similar questions. wish i didnt take the course

The Professor was a VERY responsible one. She assigned one more assignment for students to get higher mark instead of belt curve; she adjusted the teaching styles according to different situations through out the year. I would definitely choose any courses with this Professor. Thanks for bringing the Useful knowledge to us.

One thing you should be CRYSTAL CLEAR about before taking her 204 class. What you put into the course is no where near what you will get out of it. # of hours prepped for exams will have zero correlation to performance. I regret my decision instantly. Tread with caution.

Material is easy to understand, you go into the test feeling like you will ace it then the class average is in the 50's. The test questions get harder and harder, even if you do past tests, tutorials, and homework assignments.

She is fair, but her final was a little tricky as it dropped me 8 percent. I am a little worried for the 300 macro classes as we did go a little slow, and she wasn't really confident when teaching some of the concepts, which is fair since she is a micro-economist. All in all though she is a credit to the UTM economics faculty.

Easy class, easy tests. All you need to do to get an A in this course is to go to class and pay attention. All the material that she puts on the test is in the lecture slides or on the homework assignment. Textbook is optional, don't get it. It sucks.

The professor's teaching method is very easy to understand. This is her 3rd year of teaching the course so she is more confident now. I am very proactive in her class, and there really is no reason to get a bad mark...until, I wrote her SUPER HARD TEST!!!!! now, I don't even now if I could pass the course...

One of the best eco classes i've taken at UTM.  Tests answers pretty much given in lecture notes and examples.  Rarely used the book.  Just pay attention and review your notes and assigned problems and you won't have any problems.  She's a cutie too.

The final exam was identical to tutorial questions and term test. Just the numbers are different. Nothing to complain really. If you read her notes and did every single question she told us to and didn't ace the test. Don't blame on her
She ruined my GPA. That is all!

HORRIBLE professor... i was getting 83 before the final and ended up with a C+. not because i was lazy and didn't study but because most things on the final were very unexpected. she'd make the least important concept worth 40% of the final... i regret taking her course and i wouldn't recommend her to anyone.

Yes her tests are hard. yes shes young. yes shes hot. BUT i guess if you put your work into her notes and actually taking down what she says (the main parts) then you will actually do good. THE THING IS that her tests her ONLY based on her notes (which are like around 100 pages per term test). That is so much better than studying from thick book.
this is the worse eco course I ever took!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! she ruined my GPA!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Keep attending class and the textbook will be useless... don't attend class and then join the complainers!

monotone. she asks question and everyone would just stare cuz they don't know what she's talking about. can't explain theories in a clear way. tutorial questions are so unclear and subjective even with answers provided
Shes a good prof, but bad at making tests. The questions were not well weighted and students were not well prepared for the test.

I dont understand why people do bad in her class? If you attend all lectures and attempt every question she assigns I assure you, you will end up with atleast a 73 in the course. Her test questions are based of lecture notes and homework assignments so study those well.

Her midterms were average, but exam was a killer. It was super long, and consisted of only 5 big questions that were divided into many parts. All these parts were related to one another, so if you didn't know how to do one part, pretty much you're screwed. AVOID HER AT ALL COSTS AND RUN FAR AWAY WITH YOUR MONEY!! OR JUST TAKE BAILEY!!

No real teaching, fill in the blanks for notes bc that's how SHE enjoys learning. Not engaging at all, continuously keeps talking. Class is boring and a waste of time. Avoid her if possible. You've been warned.
totally ture

Some words that describe her: cute, helpful, nice, confused, hard. I actually saw ppl walk out of the final exam crying, my friend got a C+ with her is now taking eco200 with Bailey and getting OVER 100%, yes, u read right. So judge for urself, if you put A LOT of effort into her class u will get 80+, but she's really unpredictable
oh and her homework solutions are posted online for everyone before the exams which definitely helped me.

don't know why people are complaining.  if you pay attention to what she tells you to study for the exams then you will get an A every time.  I'm not a genius but i got an A in both her 202 and 204 classes.  her exam questions are exactly from the homework and tutorials.  would take her class again for sure.  plus she's super cute too.
SHE IS SO CUTE <3 , definitely the cutest prof i have ever seen.
I'll leave it at this: I've never seen people leave the exam crying before, because they think they didn't get even 10% on the exam.

she is so messed up in the lecture, and the lecture is super easy while the tests is hard.  the final is super "surpriseD"! not a single question come from any hwk and tests! everything is too detail.  she is the nightmare of us!!!  dont take her class ever!!!!  awful prof ever!!!!

she is so messed up! can't tell what's gonna be on the tests. her homework is too long, and she doesn't even have it marked BEFORE the test, so any mistakes made on the HW are made on the tests. the least she could've done is best 3 of 4. i don't care if she's new, but she has to stop treating us like her peers from a masters level class!
Horrible prof.  She gets confused very easily.  She came to class the day before the midterm and told us she taught some of the material incorrectly... you should've seen the results on that test!
Very inconsistent prof. You will have no idea how to write her test and you will not have enough time. Avoid taking this class if you can. Go with Bailey guaranteed higher mark.

Okay so this prof gives you homework before the tests happen, and they're NOTHING like that the test's are actually like! She makes the tests super hard, there's never enough time, and make the most useless questions worth so much! I don't know if you should take bailey eitehr, but shes probably just as bad!

New at teaching, her way of giving "fill in the blanks" notes makes it hard for all students. You either listen,understand and not take notes or you take notes and cannot pay attention to the lectures. As for her tests, the questions are not well weighted and often rely on the use of more algebra than economics.
Take Bailey next time. I shoud've got 100.
